# Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Use utility classes consistently
- Follow the existing color scheme
- Use responsive design patterns
- Implement proper spacing and typography

## Color Scheme
- Primary: Blue (blue-600, blue-700)
- Success: Green (green-600)
- Warning: Yellow (yellow-600)
- Error: Red (red-600)
- Neutral: Gray scale (gray-50 to gray-900)

## Component Styling Patterns

### Cards
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
```

### Buttons
```tsx
// Primary button
<button className="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-blue-600 border border-transparent rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 transition-colors">

// Secondary button
<button className="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 bg-gray-100 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-200 transition-colors">
```

### Forms
```tsx
<input className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-transparent" />
```

### Modals
```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4 z-50">
  <div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-xl max-w-2xl w-full max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto">
```

## Responsive Design
- Use `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2` for responsive grids
- Use `flex flex-col md:flex-row` for responsive layouts
- Use `text-sm md:text-base` for responsive typography
- Use `p-4 md:p-6` for responsive padding